Very few generalizations bound tailored specifically to mixtures of experts appear in the literature, and those we could find do not apply to mixtures of experts with the one-out-of-\(n\) gating mechanism. We can, however, compare our bounds to those obtained by naively applying generic PAC-Bayes generalization bounds to mixtures of experts. In this case, we need to consider classifiers of the form \((Q_{},Q)\), where \(Q_{}\) is a probability measure on \(\), and \(Q=Q_{1} Q_{n}\) is a probability measure on \(_{1}_{n}\) as before. Then, note that

